definitions.definition: An official keeper or recorder of records .

subdefinitions.definition: An officer in a university who keeps enrollment and academic achievement records.
The person responsible for record-keeping related to a museum's or archive's collection.
The chief executive officer of a judicial forum, in charge of the entire registry of the department.

definitions.definition: A doctor receiving advanced specialist training in some countries in order to become a consultant .
A service that manages the reservation of domain names .
